00:53:48.159 --> 00:53:52.697 align:middle line:84%
of a chicken and he writes
about this in his autobiography.

00:53:52.697 --> 00:53:55.099 align:middle line:84%
And then he-- I believe
he had hepatitis.

00:53:55.099 --> 00:53:56.701 align:middle line:84%
He has a particular
health condition

00:53:56.701 --> 00:53:58.569 align:middle line:84%
where his health
decline very quickly.

00:53:58.569 --> 00:54:01.138 align:middle line:84%
Even on a vegetarian diet I
think he may have still been

00:54:01.138 --> 00:54:04.075 align:middle line:84%
eating dairy or something but
his doctors said, "No, no,

00:54:04.075 --> 00:54:07.812 align:middle line:84%
no you have to continue to
eat some meat and flesh."

00:54:07.812 --> 00:54:10.715 align:middle line:84%
So, he relates his
own experience a bit

00:54:10.715 --> 00:54:15.052 align:middle line:84%
but he also talks about
the Tibetan Buddhist ethic,

00:54:15.052 --> 00:54:18.622 align:middle line:84%
this is back in the
1960s or '70s at least,

00:54:18.622 --> 00:54:23.094 align:middle line:84%
the Tibetan Buddhist ethic
of eating meat which is

00:54:23.094 --> 00:54:30.201 align:middle line:84%
that you can eat meat
but you can't kill

00:54:30.201 --> 00:54:33.270 align:middle line:90%
and you can't go and order it.

00:54:33.270 --> 00:54:36.741 align:middle line:84%
The only-- so you can't
essentially directly trigger the

00:54:36.741 --> 00:54:37.742 align:middle line:90%
killing of an animal.

00:54:37.742 --> 00:54:39.043 align:middle line:84%
>> Or order the killing
of the animal.

00:54:39.043 --> 00:54:40.578 align:middle line:84%
>> You can't order it because
then it might be killed

00:54:40.578 --> 00:54:43.581 align:middle line:84%
specifically for
you and bad karma.

00:54:43.581 --> 00:54:44.682 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:54:44.682 --> 00:54:49.186 align:middle line:84%
>> So, the dilemma is
how do we eat them?

00:54:49.186 --> 00:54:50.488 align:middle line:90%
It was a staple local diet.

00:54:50.488 --> 00:54:52.957 align:middle line:84%
They had barley bread, and
meat, and some other things

00:54:52.957 --> 00:54:54.825 align:middle line:90%
but it was real staple.

00:54:54.825 --> 00:54:58.262 align:middle line:84%
So, they would have
local Muslims do it.

00:54:58.262 --> 00:55:02.933 align:middle line:84%
So, they would farm it out just
like we do in the supermarket.

00:55:02.933 --> 00:55:04.769 align:middle line:84%
>> Isn't that ordering
it so to speak?

00:55:04.769 --> 00:55:06.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, but I don't know
exactly what you meant

00:55:06.670 --> 00:55:09.673 align:middle line:84%
by ordering, but you know,
you could go to a like I think

00:55:09.673 --> 00:55:12.943 align:middle line:84%
like a, you know, say a butcher
shop where there was meat

00:55:12.943 --> 00:55:14.879 align:middle line:84%
but you couldn't say, "I
don't see any meat here,

00:55:14.879 --> 00:55:16.580 align:middle line:84%
I'd like some meat and
then [inaudible] come

00:55:16.580 --> 00:55:18.416 align:middle line:90%
up back," you know?

00:55:18.416 --> 00:55:20.484 align:middle line:84%
[laughter] You know, so
it's a very convoluted.

00:55:20.484 --> 00:55:22.620 align:middle line:84%
>> But that's not terribly
different from what we all do

00:55:22.620 --> 00:55:24.889 align:middle line:84%
when we go to the
supermarket, really.

00:55:24.889 --> 00:55:26.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly and that's--

00:55:26.190 --> 00:55:30.161 align:middle line:84%
that's what I realized that
it was not that different.

00:55:30.161 --> 00:55:32.630 align:middle line:90%
But my sense of it was, "Gosh,

00:55:32.630 --> 00:55:34.598 align:middle line:84%
why should that be
less bad karma?"

00:55:34.598 --> 00:55:35.433 align:middle line:90%
>> You're right.

00:55:35.433 --> 00:55:36.467 align:middle line:90%
>> Should not be more bad karma?

00:55:36.467 --> 00:55:37.902 align:middle line:84%
It's like willful
ignorance [laughs].

00:55:37.902 --> 00:55:40.504 align:middle line:84%
>> Right, a will-- yes
a willful ignorance.

00:55:40.504 --> 00:55:43.007 align:middle line:84%
Was there-- you know, I've
interviewed so many people

00:55:43.007 --> 00:55:45.709 align:middle line:84%
from many different
backgrounds philosophically,

00:55:45.709 --> 00:55:48.879 align:middle line:84%
religious in terms of
religions and so forth.

00:55:48.879 --> 00:55:54.418 align:middle line:84%
And one thought that has come up
or one philosophy that has come

00:55:54.418 --> 00:55:59.223 align:middle line:84%
up a few times has been that on
a very deep and ancient level

00:55:59.223 --> 00:56:03.294 align:middle line:84%
that there has been an agreement
between the plant kingdom

00:56:03.294 --> 00:56:05.729 align:middle line:84%
and the animal kingdom,
and the animal kingdom

00:56:05.729 --> 00:56:10.401 align:middle line:84%
and the human kingdom as well
in terms of permissions to be

00:56:10.401 --> 00:56:13.137 align:middle line:84%
of service and to
give sustenance.

00:56:13.137 --> 00:56:16.040 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know that that
particularly resonates for you

00:56:16.040 --> 00:56:20.845 align:middle line:84%
but on a really deep level,
give-- just share as--

00:56:20.845 --> 00:56:24.381 align:middle line:84%
a kind of a final thought, we
only have a couple minutes left

00:56:24.381 --> 00:56:26.217 align:middle line:90%
on what this has brought back

00:56:26.217 --> 00:56:29.620 align:middle line:84%
to your life besides personal
accountability obviously.

00:56:29.620 --> 00:56:34.258 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, you know, many cultural
traditions do tell these stories

00:56:34.258 --> 00:56:39.196 align:middle line:84%
about permission and about an
agreement between the hunter

00:56:39.196 --> 00:56:41.098 align:middle line:90%
and the hunted in such.

00:56:41.098 --> 00:56:43.434 align:middle line:84%
And I don't personally
have that word view.

00:56:43.434 --> 00:56:44.568 align:middle line:90%
I didn't grow up in it.

00:56:44.568 --> 00:56:47.271 align:middle line:84%
It makes sense to me in
a way but I'm not sure.

00:56:47.271 --> 00:56:52.176 align:middle line:84%
For me when I finally
took the life of a deer,

00:56:52.176 --> 00:56:56.680 align:middle line:84%
when I finally did do that in
my fourth year as a hunter,

00:56:56.680 --> 00:57:00.417 align:middle line:84%
it was devastating and I wasn't
sure I would ever do it again,

00:57:00.417 --> 00:57:04.855 align:middle line:84%
